<HEADLINE> Durand Wins Paris-Tours Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Jacky Durand of France won the
Paris-Tours World Cup cycling race on Sunday by winning a sprint
finish against Italian Mirco Gualdi.
</P>
<P>
Durand racing for the Casino team collects 100 World Cup
points for taking the 254 kilometer race from Paris to Tours.
</P>
<P>
Gualdi, who rides for the Polti team, picks up 75 points.
Estonia's Jaan Kirsipuu, Durand's team mate, came third, 30
second behind the winner, ahead of Italians Stefano Zanini in
fourth and Nicola Minali in fifth.
</P>
<P>
Michele Bartoli, of the Asics team, could have regained his
World Cup title with a good finish on Sunday but didn't figure
among the leaders. Endtiem

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
