<HEADLINE> Cha Beats Qi in China Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Former South Korea's national
coach Cha Bum-kum led the Shenzhen Ping'an to a 2-0 victory over
Wuhan Hongjinlong, coached by former China's national coach Qi
Wusheng, in the China's first division league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Both coaches were sacked after failing to make any remarkable
performances in the World Cup qualifiers and the finals
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hongjinlong played most of the match with ten players after
Yang Xiaochun was sent as he tackled down Zhang Jun in the 31 min
utes.
</P>
<P>
Xie Feng slotted in the opener from the resulting free-kick
and set up Li Weifeng on another in the second half. The latter
headed in the second goal in the 56 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Struggling in the relegation group with three rounds left this
season, both teams needed at least two victories to secure places
in the first division.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Wanda, who has won the title in last round, showed no
sign of backfire after announcing to sell the club after its loss
in the league Cup semi-finals, beating Vanguard Huandao 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Wanda said in its announcement of withdraw from the Chinese
soccer that it could not endure the "wrong ruling" of the
referees in Chinese soccer as the team was deprived of two
penalties and eventually lost to Liaoning Tianrun 5-6 in a penal
ty shoot-out.
</P>
<P>
With the title out of hand, Shanghai Shenhua moved one step up
to secure second place after ousting the bottom Guangzhou Apollo
2-0.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other matches, Yanbian Aodong lost to the visiting
Shandong Luneng 1-0, Qingdao Hainiu upset Guangzhou Songri 2-0
and Chinese Army clinches a golden 3-0 victory from Shenyang
Haishi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
