<HEADLINE> Israel Asked to Comply with U.N. Resolutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Participants in a conference
on European-Palestinian partnership on Sunday called on Israel to
implement U.N. resolutions 242 and 338, which they deemed as the
basis for economic and social development in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which began last week and ended Sunday in the
West Bank city of Ramallah, was attended by European and
Palestinian diplomats, officials and academics, a Jerusalem-based
Palestinian press service reported.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Media and Communication Center (JMCC) quoted
European diplomats as saying that the implementation of the U.N.
resolutions, which call for Israeli withdrawal from occupied
territories, will open the way for regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The participants also urged Israeli government to halt
unilateral measures like demolishing Palestinian houses, expanding
Jewish settlements and "Judaizing" Jerusalem, the JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. administration has reportedly asked Israel to freeze
the expansion of Jewish settlements in exchange for Palestinian
agreement to refrain from building houses without permits.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat has urged
the European countries to increase their political involvement in
the region and to use their economic influence to advance the
peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
