within its capacity to protect people's life and property from
the irresponsible acts of the Sudanese authorities.
</P>
<P>
Sudan has accused Uganda of sending soldiers to fight along
with the rebel Sudanese People's Liberation Army (SPLA) against
Khartoum, a charge Kampala denied.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government also denied a report that over 500
Ugandan troops had been killed in southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Sudan launched a general mobilization across the
country by closing universities and calling on young men to take
up arms for a war that they called a war to end wars. 
