<HEADLINE> Lebanese Soldier Wounded in Israeli Shelling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese soldier was wounded on
Monday in an Israeli shelling on Lebanon's eastern province of
Bekaa.
</P>
<P>
The soldier was hit when Israeli troops shelled a post of the
Lebanese army in western Bekaa in a retaliatory attack on
Hezbollah, Lebanon's main resistance group, the Orient Radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
He is believed to be the first Lebanese soldier wounded this
year in armed clashes between Lebanese guerrillas and Israeli
forces.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, attacked a post of the
Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army (SLA) Monday morning on the
verge of the Israeli-occupied south Lebanon with machine guns and
grenades. There was no immediate report of casualties.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a so-called security zone in south Lebanon in 1985
to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border attacks
by Lebanese guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah is spearheading a guerrilla war to oust more than
1,500 Israeli troops and about 3,000 SLA militiamen out of south
Lebanon. 
</P>
