<HEADLINE> New Party Secretary for China's Hunan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) recently appointed Yang Zhengwu
secretary of the Party Committee of Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Party Central Committee said that Wang Maolin, who held the
position, will no longer be the secretary or a Standing Committee
member and member of the CPC Hunan Provincial Committee and will
be assigned to a new position.
</P>
<P>
Yang, of Tujia ethnic group, is a native of Longshan, Hunan
Province. He was appointed deputy secretary of the CPC Hunan
Provincial Committee in 1990 and governor of Hunan in 1995, and
was reelected governor of Hunan earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
He was alternate member of the 12th CPC Central Committee and
member of the 13th and 15th CPC Central Committees. 
</P>
