<HEADLINE> Thompson Named as Swimmer of Year by USA Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Jenny Thompson, the first
American since Tracy Caulkins in 1978 to win four gold medals in
the world swimming championships, was honored as the swimmer of
the year by the USA Swimming, according to the press report Mond
ay.
</P>
<P>
Thompson, who won the 100 meter freestyle and 100 butterfly
and helped the United States to two relay victories, also
received the Phillips Performance Award to sweep the top honors
at the USA Swimming convention.
</P>
<P>
Thompson's meet-record breaking perfromance in the 100
butterfly earned her the Phillips Performance Award. Her time of
58.46 was the third fastest in history and the best by an
American in 17 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
