<HEADLINE> Cardoso Wins Brazil Elections: Partial Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President
Fernando Henrique Cardoso won reelection with slightly more than
50 percent of the vote after counting just over half the ballots.
electoral officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
With 53 percent of the ballots counted, the Social Democratic
leader had 50.47 percent of the vote compared with 34.81 percent
for his main rival, left-wing coalition leader Luiz Inacio "Lula"
da Silva.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso, 67, needs 50 percent plus one vote to win Sunday's
election without having to go through a second round.
</P>
<P>
While Cardoso appeared to hold on to his majority, final
results in guberanatorial elections showed a second round of
voting would be needed on October 25 in Rio de Janeiro and
Brasilia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
