<HEADLINE> 15 Burnt to Death in Tanker Crash in E. Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were burnt to
death on the spot while three others died later in hospital when
a commercial bus crashed into a fuel tanker at Wirenkyrirem, near
Amanfrom in east of Ghana at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
It took a combined team of police and local firemen about nine
hours to put out the blaze from the collision, which eyewitnesses
described as "horrifying", the Ghana News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said the accident occurred at about 23:00 hours
Sunday as a result of wrongful overtaking by the 47-seater bus.
</P>
<P>
"It collided head-on with the tanker whose driver
unsuccessfully attempted to avoid it," police superintendent
Oscar Antwi confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Antwi said Sunday's accident is the third in a month involving
fuel tankers in that particular stretch of the road "resulting in
considerable damage to life and property."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police have requested members of the public
whose relatives traveled on the route at the weekend to contact
the local hospital to identify the victims whose charred bodies
are beyond recognition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
