<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Carl Merrill, a road racer
from the United States who twice won the North American Rally
Championship, died after suffering a heart attack while racing in
Prescott, Ariz, the United States, on Sunday.
</P>
