<HEADLINE> Chinese, Kazakh Defence Ministers Hold Informal Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh Defense Minister Mukhtar
Altynbayev, in a meeting with Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian
this afternoon, said that Kazakhstan supports China's
reunification and will never allow anyone to use his country as a
base for activities, attempting to split China.
</P>
<P>
The two men met in the capital of China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region to discuss putting into practice the consensus
reached during President Jiang Zemin's July visit to Kazakhstan on
reinforcing long-term good-neighborly relations oriented to the
21st century and developing cooperation between the Chinese and
Kazakh armed forces.
</P>
<P>
A solid foundation has been set up between the two countries
since they established diplomatic ties, Chi said, pointing to the
close political, economic, science, technological, and cultural
relations.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two armed forces have also gone smoothly,
he said, adding that he believes that developing relations
between the two countries and their armed forces is conducive to
the peace and stability in the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Altynbayev said that the informal meeting show the sound
cooperative relations between the two armed forces and the two
countries, and expressed the hope that they will be further
strengthened.  
</P>
</TEXT>
