<HEADLINE> Congolese (K) Rebels Launch Offensive on Kindu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The rebels fighting to oust
President Laurent Kabila from power have announced a major
offensive on Kindu, capital of Maniema Province in the east of
the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Rebel-controlled radio Bukavu monitored in Cyangugu, Rwanda,
said Monday morning that the Congolese rebels arrived in the city
earlier than planned on Sunday, moving on three fronts, with the
ultimate aim of overruning it, the Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Intense fighting was signaled at the Kindu airport which hy5( 1M1%5P=BYAQUI@=
9ju{nday. But there has been no
independent confirmation of the capture.
</P>
<P>
Radio Bukavu further reported that Kindu had been chosen by
Kabila's loyalist forces and their allies as their general
headquarters from where they had been planning to launch a major
counter-offensive to retake the towns fallen to the rebels since
August 2, when the uprising started.
</P>
<P>
The reported attack on Kindu followed the seizure of a string
of towns near Kindu, notably Kalima, Ubundu, as well as Buta and
Isiro in Oriental Province last week.
</P>
<P>
The rebel officials had recently declared that the fall of
Bunia could trigger the surrendering of other towns and
provinces.
</P>
<P>
Kindu is a gateway to both Kasai provinces, known for being
rich in several minerals, notably diamonds. The next target
appears to be Lubumbashi, the second-largest city of the DRC.
</P>
