<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Data to Be Put on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange (KSE)
will put its data of bourse trading on the Internet which will be
accessible to all investors in and outside Kuwait, KSE general
director Hisham Al-Otaibi said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference here, Al-Otaibi said the service,
due to be offered from October 15, will include data on the volume
of shares, after closing and live broadcasts of the trading.
</P>
<P>
He added that as part of its information upgrading scheme, the
KSE would sell pager sets, furnishing the clients with all
necessary data about daily trading from opening till closing.
</P>
<P>
Traders will be able to compare share prices with the previous
day's closing and read names of the companies involved in trading
as pronounced in Arabic but appearing in Latin figures, he said.
</P>
<P>
Those who obtain the new device will be able to check the lists
including names of companies, number of stocks and share prices,
he added.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed to another project to furnish the clients with
the technical capacity to vocally inquire about trading by means
of telephone or pager at any time during the day.
</P>
<P>
But he said that securing such a service would not be an easy
task considering the fact that prices of traded stocks change in
seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
