<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Factories Making Way For More Residential Buildings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Many of Shanghai's chimneys,
the longtime symbol of factories, have been demolished in urban
areas since the late 1980s to make way for more residential
housing and commercial buildings.
</P>
<P>
A thousand of the tall stacks have been destroyed and replaced
with an equal number of tall buildings, more than 70 percent of
which are residential buildings.
</P>
<P>
People in the Xinhualu Residential District used to suffer from
exhaust gas from nearby factories, but 70 percent of the factories
have been relocated and the people are now living in new high-rises
on the site of the factories.
</P>
<P>
One pharmaceutical factory that went back at least 89 years was
moved from the west part of Huaihai Road. The site is now used for
apartment or office buildings. The factory is now on a new
12-hectare site in the suburbs that is nearly 11 times the
original site.
</P>
<P>
Moving or closing the factories over the past decade has meant
a reduction of 180 million cubic meters of waste gas and 14 tons
of smog and dust daily in urban areas, according to Shanghai's
environmental protection department.
</P>
<P>
Some old factory sites are now being used for service trades
like real estate, trade, or finance that do not harm the
environment. Two-thirds of the city's factories are expected to be
relocated or shifted to service trades by the year 2010, and
service trades are expected to account for 60 percent of
Shanghai's GDP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981005.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Chinese Leather Distribution Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Tong'erbao Economic Zone in
northeast China's Liaoning Province has become China's largest
leather distribution center.
</P>
<P>
The center is 20 km northwest of the city of Liaoyang. It has
30 factories each producing 50,000 leather garments annually and
one producing 500,000 units.
</P>
<P>
It has seven trading halls with 100,000 sq.m. of floor space
and handles 50,000 leather garments in 130 varieties and
specifications each day.
</P>
<P>
It did three billion yuan in business last year and had pre-tax
profits of 290 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Its products sell well in all parts of China and in a dozen of
countries and regions. 
</P>
