<HEADLINE> Expressway Linking Beijing With City Of Zhangjiakou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- China is building a 3-billion
yuan (361.5 million U.S. dollars) expressway linking the capital,
Beijing, with the city of Zhangjiakou in Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Zhangjiakou expressway is expected to be finished
in three years and will cut the travel time between the two cities
from four hours to two hours, the Communications Ministry said
today.
</P>
<P>
It is part of a national highway from Dandong to Lhasa and will
be an important economic and cultural exchange route for the
western part of China and will play an important role in farm and
sideline produce distribution, shipping Datong coal, and speeding
up economic development in poverty-stricken areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
