<HEADLINE> Italy Focus at Asia Pacific Leather Fair in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- World fashion industry
sensation Italy has once again become the focus country at the
Asia Pacific Leather Fair (APLF) Fashion and Finished Products --
Autumn Show which opened at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center here Monday.
</P>
<P>
And for the first time, the Autumn Show presents a Trend Forum
to define the fashion mood of the Spring-Summer '99.
</P>
<P>
"Italy is the biggest European exporter of shoes to this area
of the world, and has participated in the APLF since the very
beginning," said Leonardo Radicati, Italian Trade Commissioner in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Apart from organizing a pavilion of more than 130 exhibitors to
show their finest products for the coming new season, Italy has
organized a variety of special events including fashion shows.
</P>
<P>
The Asian market remained attractive although the region is
suffering from the consequences of the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The Asian market is still an important market of high
potential, which continues to offer good prospects for long-term
investors and corporations in particular when the economies come
out of their down cycle. The Asia Pacific Leather Fair is
committed to support the industry on better preparing for the
rebound," said a spokesman for managers of the event Miller
Freeman Asia Ltd.
</P>
<P>
A total of 624 exhibitors from 25 countries and regions are
participating in the three-day event. Apart from Italy,
Bangladesh, Chinese mainland, France, Indonesia, Portugal, Spain
and Taiwan region have organized their group pavilions at the Show.
</P>
<P>
The Autumn Show features the latest leather fashion collections
in sections of footwear, garments, finished goods and accessories
and components, and seminars will be held during the fair to give
updates and practical insights of the industry, according to the
organizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
