<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday on lack of fresh leads
and a fall in major regional markets.
</P>
<P>
Investors were sidelined but some steady bluechips enabled key
indices to limit their losses as they moved along a narrow range.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index lost 2.96
points to 360.10, the all-share Emas Index lost 0.89 of a point to
95.66 and the Industrial Index lost 0.82 of a point to 719.55
while the Second Board Index lost 0.96 of a point to 90.11.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 373 to 156 while 121 counters
were unchanged and 267 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 79.096 million shares valued at
98.951 million ringgit (about 26.039 million U.S. dollars) from
121.484 million shares worth 177.224 million ringgit (about 46.637
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover declined to 76.191 million shares
valued at 94.426 million ringgit (about 24.848 million U.S.
dollars) from 116.846 million shares worth 170.845 million ringgit
(about 44.959 million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover shrank to 2.905 million shares worth
4.525 million ringgit (about 1.19 million U.S. dollars) from 4.638
million shares valued at 6.379 million ringgit (about 1.678
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover dropped to 3.770 million shares worth 8.291
million ringgit (about 2.181 million U.S. dollars) from 8.204
million shares worth 3.465 million ringgit (about 0.911 million
U.S. dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
