<HEADLINE> Quakes Jolt Different Parts of Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Several earthquakes jolted three
southwestern provinces of Iran on Monday, but there was no report
on possible casualties, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
A quake of 5.3 degrees on the open-ended Richter scale hit
southern part of Ilam province at 0550 hours local time (0220
GMT), at least 100 houses have been damaged in Darreh Shahr city
and its surrounding villages.
</P>
<P>
The seismological base of Kermanshah, in western Iran,
registered the epicenter of the quake 115 kilometers from the
base in the vicinity of Darreh Shahr and Kouhdasht in Lorestan
province.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday another quake of 4.8 degree rocked Darreh Shahr at
0413 hours local time (0043 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, two mild earthquakes measuring at 3.2 and 3.3
degrees jolted the town of Sisakht in southwestern province of
Kohkiloyeh-Boyerahmad at 0311 and 0741 hours local time (2341 and
0411 GMT) respectively.
</P>
<P>
The seismological center in Shiraz, southern province of Fars,
registered the epicenter of the tremors 180 kilometers north of
Shiraz between the towns of Sisakht and Yasouj. 
</P>
</TEXT>
