<HEADLINE> Mubarak to Visit Ankara on Turkey-Syria Disputes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
will visit Turkey Tuesday to seek ways to defuse the on-going
crisis between Turkey and Syria, a Turkish foreign ministry
spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, Necati Utkan added "there is not a designation for
mediator. For mediation, the two sides have to assign a mediator."
</P>
<P>
"Does Syria announce that Egypt is her mediator? Then why do we
have to make such a statement?" he asked.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that the hope for a diplomatic solution to the crisis
has not come to an end, Utkan said: "We will listen to President
Mubarak. We expect President Mubarak to bring us information or at
least impression."
</P>
<P>
Turkey has stepped up its accusation of Syria's alleged support
to the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK), which has been
fighting since 1984 for autonomy in southeastern Turkey. Tensions
mounted after Ankara reportedly massed troops along borders with
Syria.
</P>
<P>
And Syria has accused Turkey of forming military alliance
with Israel, saying that it threatens Arab security and
undermines Syria's bargaining position in peace talks with the
Jewish state. 
