<HEADLINE> Connors Wins BTI Senior Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Jimmy Connors of the United
States beat Mats Wilander to win the BTI Champions senior tennis
tournament in Atlanta, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Connors beat Wilander 6-2, 6-1 to win his first career win
over Wilander, who had beaten the American each of their five
meetings on the men's tour.
</P>
<P>
The victory was Connors' fourth senior circuit title of the
1998-99 season and netted him 40,000 U.S. dollars. Wilander, who
was making his Nuveen Tour debut, won 25,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
"I'd say that was one of the better matches I've played in the
last six years," said Connors. "It was one of those days when I
was seeing the ball well and hitting everything cleanly."
</P>
<P>
In the doubles final, Howard Herr and Ned Caswell failed in
their bid to become the first qualifying team to win a Nuveen
Tour event, losing 6-4, 7-6 (7-5) in the final to Johan Kriek and
Mel Purcell.
</P>
<P>
The BTI Champions is the 12th event on the 1998-99 worldwide
senior tennis circuit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
