<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Beijing recorded a 26.1 percent
rise in individual income taxes in the first eight months this
year, with total tax revenues hitting 2.61 billion yuan (314
million US dollars), according to Beijing Tax Bureau.
</P>
