<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Singapore Dollar Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) launched Sunday a Singapore dollar (SGS)
domestic bond issue for the amount of 300 million SGS (about 178
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This transaction, IFC's debut Singapore dollar issue, is also
the first of its kind launched by a non-resident issuer in the
Singapore market.
</P>
<P>
The three-year bonds carried a semi-annual coupon of 4.5
percent per annum and were issued at 99.446 percent of par.
</P>
<P>
The lead manager of the issue is Citicorp Investment Bank
(Singapore) Limited.
</P>
<P>
Co-lead managers are Development Bank of Singapore Limited and
Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation. The issue is expected to be
placed with institutional investors in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and the largest source
of financing for private sector companies in developing
countries. Its long-term debt is rated triple-A by Standard and
Poor's and Moody's Investors Service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
