<HEADLINE> DPRK Newspaper Criticizes IAEA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 5 (Xinhua) -- An official newspaper of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Sunday criticized the
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) for urging the country
to carry out comprehensive implementation of the nuclear assurance
accord.
</P>
<P>
A commentary in the Rodong Sinmum said the DPRK would take
nuclear measures under agreements with the United States, which
promised to build new light-water reactors for the DPRK, not under
the IAEA's nuclear assurance accord.
</P>
<P>
With the light-water reactors not yet built, the IAEA's demand
for "checks of nuclear facilities" and its urge for the DPRK "to
implement the nuclear assurance" are simply ridiculous, the
commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The article said the IAEA had better stand aside and watch the
DPRK and the U.S. implement the agreements reached between them,
because the DPRK has not forgotten the IAEA's hostilities towards
it in the past. 
</P>
