<HEADLINE> Sihanouk Arrives in Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's King Norodom
Sihanouk arrived here Monday from the northwestern town of Siem
Reap.  Meeting the king and queen at the Pochentong Airport are
Chea Sim, president of the Cambodian People's Party, and First
Prime Minister Ung Hout. Second Prime Minister Hun Sen was not
present at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Prince Ranariddh, president of Funcinpec, and Sam Rainsy,
president of his self-named party, the country's main opposition
political party leaders, are still abroad.
</P>
<P>
The king last came here on December 3, 1997, and stayed until
January 5 when he abruptly left the capital for Beijing. He has
been at his royal residence in Siem Reap since April 11.
</P>
<P>
King Sihanouk decided earlier to delay his trip to Beijing for
medical treatment after senior government officials urged him to
stay until a coalition government is formed.
</P>
<P>
It is widely believed that the king's stay in the country will
ease the tensions between the rival parties, led by Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen and by Prince Ranariddh and Sam Rainsy
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said King Sihanouk is respected by all sides and is in
a position to help end the current political deadlock. He will
also help push the formation of the new government as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
The working groups of the three main parties is to hold their
second working session Monday afternoon to discuss how top
Assembly posts and committee chairmanships would be allocated. But
the king is not expected to participate in the working groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
