<HEADLINE> Private Enterprises Flourishing in South China Coastal City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The fast growing private sector
is now businesses playing an increasingly important role in
economic development of Shantou, a coastal open city in south
China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 1,992 private enterprises with over 15,900
employees were registered in the first eight months of this
year. By the end of August, Shantou had more than 9,800 private
enterprises, employing over 100,000 people and with a total
registered capital of 6.68 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of large private enterprises is on the
rise. Of the nearly 10,000 private firms, 73 each have a
registered capital of more than over five million yuan, and 30
enterprises each over 100 million yuan. Some of them have turned
from dealing with daily necessities and repair to modern
productive, technology-intensive and export-oriented companies.
</P>
<P>
Wit the improvement in the industrial structure, local private
enterprises now are engaged in various fields including industry,
commerce, transportation and services.
</P>
<P>
They have also become an important sources of the city's
taxes. Last year, they paid more than 360 million yuan in taxes.
</P>
</TEXT>
