<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Commemorates World Habitat Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A series of activities have been
organized in Sri Lanka Monday to commemorate the World Habitat
Day, declared by the U.N. Center for Human settlements on the
theme of "Safer Cities."
</P>
<P>
According to official sources Monday, a conference on the theme
"Safer Cities" will be held Monday and Tuesday in Colombo to mark
the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The National Housing Development Authority (NDHA) will confer
land ownership on 10,000 families in 57 housing projects in
Colombo and its suburbs. These families will get deeds for a
50-year lease period, the sources from the Ministry of Housing
said.
</P>
