<HEADLINE> Beijing Introduces New Watermelon Variety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The agricultural sector in
Beijing, the Chinese capital, plans to introduce a new variety of
watermelon seeds to replace the popular Jing Xin No.1 variety
currently in production.
</P>
<P>
Some 747 seeds sent into space over a 15 day period two years
ago were subjected to radiation in a vacuum environment basically
free of gravitational forces, according to today's edition of
the Beijing Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences and
Beijing Municipal Academy of Agricultural Sciences introduced the
new melon variety to the market during this year's National Day
holidays (October 1-4).
</P>
<P>
Experts note that the new variety has a higher content of both
sugar and vitamins and is more appealing to the eye.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the so-called "space watermelon" to be grown
extensively in the southern part of the city over the next two
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
