<HEADLINE> Former Swiss President Delamuraz Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Former Swiss President Jean-
Pascal Delamuraz died of liver cancer Sunday at the age of 62, the
Swiss federal government announced.
</P>
<P>
Delamuraz, who twice served as rotating president in 1989 and
1996 respectively, resigned in March as economic minister for
health reasons.
</P>
<P>
He underwent an operation for liver cancer in 1997, following
heart operations in 1992 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
He was defense minister in 1984 and economic minister from 1987
until his resignation. 
</P>
