<HEADLINE> Rental Cars Gain Popularity in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Xie Weimin, a resident of
Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province, rented a car
for 800 yuan (97 U.S. dollars) over the National Day holiday
period to take his family to nearby Ningbo holidays.
</P>
<P>
Xie said the rental car provided the family a convenient means
of travelling to destination they desired.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of licensed Chinese drivers in urban areas are
renting motor vehicles for sightseeing or visits to relatives and
friends.
</P>
<P>
Car rentals have boomed in many part of China in recent years since
many licensed drivers do not as yet own vehicles.
</P>
<P>
A dozen-odd car rental agencies have opened in Hangzhou, with
more than 80 percent of their fleets under rental contracts on any
given day. Agencies are, in fact, unable to meet demand on
holidays, according to an official with the Zhejiang Provincial
Transportation Department.
</P>
<P>
Industry observers attribute the popularity of car rentals to
the constantly rising living standards of Chinese citizens and the
nation's improved transportation system.
</P>
<P>
The manager of one Hangzhou car rental agency said that his
agency's 40 vehicles were booked two weeks prior to National
Day. He noted that most vehicles were used for trips to nearby
scenic sites such as Ningbo, Shaoxing and Qiandaohu Lake.
</P>
</TEXT>
