<HEADLINE> Fujian-Taiwan Trade Developing Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Trade between east China's Fujian
and Taiwan provinces continued to develop in the first eight
months of this year, despite the influence of the Asian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official said that during the
January-August period, the value of total imports and exports
between Fujian and Taiwan was 1.66 billion U.S. dollars, up 5.9
percent over the same 1997 period, and accounting for 12.7 percent
of the mainland's total trade volume with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
During this period, overseas-funded enterprises in Fujian had
1.36 billion U.S. dollars of trade volume with Taiwan, up 6.1
percent and accounting for 82 percent of the province's total
trade volume with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The processing industry, the major component of Fujian's trade
with Taiwan, generated 1.16 billion U.S. dollars in the first
eight months to August, up nearly five percent over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Fujian also optimized its trade structure with Taiwan, with
exports of primary products reduced, and those of manufactured
products increased.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that exports of primary products during the
January-August period generated 50 million U.S. dollars, down 20
percent, and those of manufactured products, 180 million
U.S. dollars, up 20 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Fujian-Taiwan trade volume has grown at an average
annual rate of 6.2 percent, and total trade volume has increased
from 2.02 billion U.S. dollars in 1993 to 2.57 billion
U.S. dollars in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
