<HEADLINE> Stimulant Drug Tablets Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
more than 656,000 tablets of amphetamine, a stimulant drug, in the
country's eastern Shan state last month, the official newspaper
The New Light of Myanmar reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of regional
intelligence unit, armymen and special anti-drug squad who
searched a car at the Tabin checkpoint in Kengtung on September
24.
</P>
<P>
The local police station has taken action against two people in
connection with the case under Myanmar's Narcotic Drug and
Psychotropic Substances Law, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on September 15, the authorities also seized 498,000
stimulant drug tablets in the same area, taking action against
three people involved in the trafficking.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 8.49 million
stimulant drug tablets have been confiscated by the Myanmar
authorities in the first nine months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
