<HEADLINE> Rios, Williams Win Grand Slam Cup Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelo Rios overcame back
pain to beat American Andre Agassi over five sets to win the
Grand Slam Cup and prize money of 1.3 million U.S. dollars on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
American teenager Venus Williams snatched 800,000 dollars
after nipping Swiss Patty Schnyder in the women's final.
</P>
<P>
Rios, ranked third in the world, said he almost considered
quitting after being kept on court for just under three hours
before subduing Agassi 6-4, 2-6, 7-6, 5-7, 6-3 when the American
double-faulted on the Chilean's second match point.
</P>
<P>
"My back started hurting yesterday and I thought about not
playing," said the 22-year-old Rios.
</P>
<P>
Williams, 18, downed her 19-year-old rival 6-2, 3-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
"I really wanted this title," said Williams. "I played pretty
well in the first set, then she picked it up a bit in the second.
I guess I just played that much better." 
</P>
</TEXT>
