<HEADLINE> Medical Program Helps People In Western China Regain Their Sight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, October 5 (Xinhua) -- In northwest China's Qinghai
Province, 1,814 cataract patients have regained the use of their
eyes in the past 5 months thanks to members of a state-sponsored
medical team who performed surgery for free.
</P>
<P>
The team members were part of a 'Sight First China Action'
program that was started in 1997 by the Ministry of Health, the
Chinese Disabled Persons Federation, and Lions Club
International. They began began working in the province in May and
have performed the operations on people suffering from cataracts
in 12 poverty-stricken counties.
</P>
<P>
Team members have gone to 4 prefectures in the province where
poor hospitals meant many difficulties and much inconvenience.
</P>
