<HEADLINE> U.S. Grouped with Brazil in FIFA Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The United States was drawn
Sunday in the same group with World Cup champion Brazil, World
Cup runner-up France and Oceania champion New Zealand in January
at Guadelajara, Mexico, in the FIFA Confederations Cup.
</P>
<P>
The other first-round group, which will play in Mexico City,
has Bolivia, Egypt, Mexico and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The tournament originally invited only the champions of FIFA's
continental confederations, but since European champion Germany
decided to pull out, the United States got the chance to fill the
spot.
</P>
<P>
The United States, which lost to Mexico in the North and
Central American and Caribbean championship final, was the second
finisher in the continent.
</P>
<P>
After winding up last in the 32 nations at the World Cup last
summer, the U.S. national team will be formed in this month, with
D.C. United coach Bruce Arena expected to take the head coach
position. He is the only American among the four candidates for
the post.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. team will play New Zealand on January 10, take on
Brazil on January 13 and close the first round against France on
January 15. 
</P>
